================================================================================
Third-party Dart / Flutter packages
================================================================================

Lighthouse AAC depends on open-source Dart and Flutter packages declared in
pubspec.yaml. Each package retains its own license.

The CANONICAL, always-current list of every bundled package and its full
license text is the in-app "Open-source licences" screen (Settings > About >
Open-source licences). It uses Flutter's showLicensePage to auto-aggregate the
license of every Dart/Flutter package compiled into the binary, so it cannot
drift from what actually ships and supersedes any hand-maintained list here.

Notable runtime dependencies include: flutter / flutter_test (BSD 3-Clause),
flutter_riverpod and riverpod_annotation (MIT), isar_community /
isar_community_flutter_libs (Apache-2.0), flutter_tts (MIT), just_audio (MIT),
record (BSD 3-Clause), share_plus and path_provider (BSD 3-Clause),
flutter_email_sender (Apache-2.0), device_info_plus / package_info_plus /
shared_preferences (BSD 3-Clause), http (BSD 3-Clause), crypto (BSD 3-Clause),
image_picker / file_selector (BSD 3-Clause). The in-app screen is authoritative
for the exact set and versions.

Dev-only dependencies (build tooling, lints, code generators) are excluded
from the shipped binary and listed in pubspec.yaml under dev_dependencies.
